SIMPLE: predisposition
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Predisposition
<hw>Pre*dis`po*si"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>pre-</ets> + <ets>disposition</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧disposition</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
predisposing, or the state of being predisposed; previous inclination,
tendency, or propensity; predilection; -- applied to the mind; <as>as, a
<ex>predisposition</ex> to anger</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> inclination; tendency; predilection;
propensity.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Previous fitness or adaptation to any change,
impression, or purpose; susceptibility; -- applied to material things;
<as>as, the <ex>predisposition</ex> of the body to
disease</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Predominance</ent>⟦br⟧
